MPUMALANGA police are investigating cases of murder and attempted murder after a 40-year-old man allegedly shot dead his wife and two kids on Friday, 27 November. Colonel Donald Mdluli said relatives made the gruesome discovery of their bodies in separate bedrooms. “The wife was shot three times in her back, while an 18-month-old boy and a seven-year-old boy were shot in the head. The dad sustained injuries to his left ear and was found in the same room where the seven-year-old’s body was discovered.” Mdluli said a gun was found on the scene. “A nine-year-old girl was also shot on the right and left hand, as well as on the head. Fortunately, she was found breathing and was taken to hospital.” Investigations are underway.